==English==
{{see|Miserere}}

===Etymology===
From [[Latin]] ''miserēre'' (have pity), first word of the 51st [[Psalm]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
# a prayer for mercy.
# an expression of [[lamentation]] or [[complaint]].
# a medieval dagger, used for the mercy stroke to a wounded foe; [[misericord]].

